WEBVTT

00:19.632 --> 00:21.174
[birds tweeting]

00:33.507 --> 00:35.007
[water trickling]

00:43.674 --> 00:45.132
[birds squawk]

02:47.840 --> 02:49.174
I have some more material.

02:50.674 --> 02:52.340
It seems you will have
to identify and secure

02:52.424 --> 02:54.382
the precise location
of his death.

02:54.465 --> 02:58.132
By which I mean
the exact spot on the floor.

02:59.632 --> 03:01.299
And tell Varney there is
definitely evidence

03:01.382 --> 03:03.799
of a transmission mirror
in the possession of the court

03:03.882 --> 03:05.382
at Targoviste.

03:05.465 --> 03:07.757
I'm working to track down
more information.

03:15.215 --> 03:17.257
From Carmilla's private stock.

03:17.340 --> 03:20.840
Now show me the map of hell
you told me about,

03:20.924 --> 03:24.007
or I'll tell her what you've
been doing with her shoes.

03:24.090 --> 03:25.090
[grunts quietly]

03:34.424 --> 03:35.924
[sizzling]

03:44.340 --> 03:45.715
Morning.

03:45.799 --> 03:47.049
Evening.

03:48.340 --> 03:50.424
[grunts and sighs]

03:50.507 --> 03:52.049
Fuck!

03:52.132 --> 03:54.090
You broke it.

03:54.174 --> 03:56.257
[sighs]
Half these billets are bad.

03:56.340 --> 03:59.882
Your vampire blacksmiths
didn't follow my specifications.

03:59.965 --> 04:04.132
A bad workman always blames
his vampires.

04:04.215 --> 04:05.507
-[billet sizzling]
-[scoffs]

04:05.590 --> 04:07.757
Don't you have anything
better to do?

04:07.840 --> 04:09.257
Not right now.

04:09.340 --> 04:11.632
Striga and Morana
have been away for weeks,

04:11.715 --> 04:13.382
surveying the territories
to be annexed.

04:13.465 --> 04:16.465
Carmilla is drawing maps.

04:17.549 --> 04:18.799
[sighs]

04:18.882 --> 04:20.174
It seems the time
when diplomacy

04:20.257 --> 04:24.382
was required for anything
has passed.

04:24.465 --> 04:26.674
Ah, so you're bored.

04:28.049 --> 04:30.299
No. You're worried.

04:31.424 --> 04:32.882
Shush.

04:32.965 --> 04:35.924
Lenore, are they sidelining you?

04:36.007 --> 04:37.340
They're not...

04:37.424 --> 04:39.132
It's not like that.

04:39.215 --> 04:42.007
Or, at least, they wouldn't
think of it like that.

04:42.090 --> 04:44.090
Our lives have entered
a new phase.

04:44.174 --> 04:45.507
Diplomacy, negotiations,

04:45.590 --> 04:47.882
these are things
of the past now.

04:47.965 --> 04:50.674
Hmm. Which makes you
a thing of the past,

04:50.757 --> 04:52.382
and that is bothering you.

04:53.465 --> 04:54.799
Look...

04:54.882 --> 04:58.632
Carmilla's plan
buys us security

04:58.715 --> 05:00.257
for hundreds of years.

05:02.549 --> 05:05.174
I'm a child of war, Hector.

05:06.424 --> 05:08.382
I was born
in a castle like this.

05:08.465 --> 05:10.882
My parents died
when English soldiers

05:10.965 --> 05:13.465
climbed up the toilet chutes
with knives in their teeth.

05:15.132 --> 05:17.007
I'd seen enough war
before I was five years old,

05:17.090 --> 05:20.799
and life didn't get better
after that.

05:21.924 --> 05:23.882
But I will never be comfortable

05:23.965 --> 05:27.382
with the idea that the best way
to end war

05:27.465 --> 05:31.299
is to kill most of the people
and cage the rest.

05:32.715 --> 05:34.965
Well, you are a diplomat.

05:35.049 --> 05:36.215
[sighs]

05:36.299 --> 05:37.674
Well, none of this will matter

05:37.757 --> 05:39.507
if you don't make
that bloody hammer.

05:39.590 --> 05:41.340
Why can't you just wave
your fingers like a wizard

05:41.424 --> 05:43.549
to raise the dead,
or whatever?

05:43.632 --> 05:46.507
[Hector] The forgemaster
works through an instrument.

05:46.590 --> 05:48.507
That may be the worst
justification

05:48.590 --> 05:51.340
for a man holding his penis
that I've ever heard.

05:51.424 --> 05:52.840
Oh, my God.

05:52.924 --> 05:54.882
And I am 200 years old.

05:54.965 --> 05:56.174
[sighs]
Look...

05:56.257 --> 05:57.674
I am a forgemaster.

05:57.757 --> 05:59.715
I didn't invent the name,
all right?

05:59.799 --> 06:01.340
That's just what they call us.

06:01.424 --> 06:03.590
And the magic has to be focused
through an instrument,

06:03.674 --> 06:06.257
like breath being pushed
through a flute.

06:06.340 --> 06:08.840
This isn't getting any better.

06:08.924 --> 06:11.257
I need the bloody hammer.
Is that better?

06:11.340 --> 06:12.840
So use a bloody hammer.

06:12.924 --> 06:15.424
There must be a thousand
bloody hammers around here.

06:15.507 --> 06:17.049
No, it's got to be special.

06:17.132 --> 06:18.549
[scoffs]

06:18.632 --> 06:20.507
Your special hammer.

06:20.590 --> 06:22.132
[laughs]
Would you stop?

06:22.215 --> 06:23.757
It has to be made from scratch,

06:23.840 --> 06:25.424
in a very particular way,

06:25.507 --> 06:27.299
or else it won't work.

06:27.382 --> 06:29.465
Like a flute with no holes.

06:29.549 --> 06:31.132
Right.

06:31.215 --> 06:33.215
-For fingering.
-[laughs]

06:33.299 --> 06:34.799
Would you stop?

06:34.882 --> 06:37.549
So when you blow it,
nothing comes out.

06:37.632 --> 06:38.965
Good god, woman.

06:39.049 --> 06:40.965
I'm bored, and it's fun
to horrify you.

06:41.049 --> 06:42.965
Indulge me.

06:43.049 --> 06:45.799
And think of something
to tell Carmilla.

06:45.882 --> 06:47.674
She's getting very cross.

06:47.757 --> 06:50.174
Oh, dear. How sad.

06:50.257 --> 06:52.090
Never mind.

06:52.174 --> 06:53.965
Seriously.

06:54.049 --> 06:57.924
You've supposedly been making
your magic hammer for weeks.

06:58.007 --> 07:00.382
Couldn't you make
something simpler?

07:00.465 --> 07:03.632
A stick, or a coin,
or something?

07:03.715 --> 07:05.507
We all use different things.

07:05.590 --> 07:07.840
Isaac used a knife.

07:07.924 --> 07:09.424
A hammer works better for me.

07:09.507 --> 07:13.007
Well, make it work faster.

07:13.090 --> 07:15.090
If Carmilla loses her temper,

07:15.174 --> 07:17.799
I won't be able to stand
in front of you for long.

07:17.882 --> 07:19.799
You'd stand in front of me?

07:19.882 --> 07:21.799
I've been doing it for weeks.

07:21.882 --> 07:23.924
Huh. Yes.

07:24.924 --> 07:26.257
Yes, I suppose you have.

07:26.340 --> 07:28.674
Well, thank you.

07:28.757 --> 07:30.007
I'm working on it.

07:31.299 --> 07:33.465
You know what I'm going to say.

07:33.549 --> 07:34.715
Hmm.

07:34.799 --> 07:36.299
Work faster.

07:36.382 --> 07:37.632
Yes.

07:37.715 --> 07:39.924
Yes, but it needs to be perfect,

07:40.007 --> 07:43.299
or nothing will come out
of the end.

07:43.382 --> 07:45.632
Ugh, you're disgusting.

07:57.174 --> 07:59.590
Has Hector made
his fucking hammer yet?

08:00.840 --> 08:02.382
He's still working on it.

08:02.465 --> 08:04.007
He's stalling.

08:04.090 --> 08:06.257
He's too simple for that.

08:07.924 --> 08:09.882
-No.
-No?

08:09.965 --> 08:11.715
No.

08:11.799 --> 08:14.132
There's a deviousness in him.

08:15.340 --> 08:16.924
Would you suspect a rag doll

08:17.007 --> 08:19.549
of planning to steal
your coin purse?

08:19.632 --> 08:24.382
You mistake that puppy thing
for being placid and stupid.

08:25.465 --> 08:26.965
He can kill.

08:27.049 --> 08:29.257
He tried, once.

08:29.340 --> 08:31.465
It was half-hearted at best.

08:32.674 --> 08:34.174
Mm. See?

08:34.257 --> 08:36.424
See what? You weren't there.

08:36.507 --> 08:38.507
He was confused and frightened,

08:38.590 --> 08:40.674
and barely even knew
what he was doing.

08:41.507 --> 08:43.007
I'm warning you.

08:43.090 --> 08:44.590
All right?

08:44.674 --> 08:46.674
I'm just warning you.

08:46.757 --> 08:50.257
Please, would Dracula have kept
him around in his own castle

08:50.340 --> 08:52.215
if he were that dangerous?

08:52.299 --> 08:53.674
[sighs]

08:54.715 --> 08:57.090
I would have liked that castle.

08:57.174 --> 08:59.257
Dracula's castle?

08:59.382 --> 09:00.757
Yes.

09:00.840 --> 09:03.840
I didn't see a lot of it,
in the end.

09:03.924 --> 09:05.132
But I'm sure it was full

09:05.215 --> 09:08.507
of interesting
and wonderful things.

09:08.590 --> 09:12.590
I am compelled to point out that
you already have a nice castle.

09:12.674 --> 09:14.757
Why would you want his?

09:14.840 --> 09:18.840
Because I take things away
from stupid, evil old men.

09:18.924 --> 09:20.215
It's what I do.

09:20.299 --> 09:22.049
I've always done it.

09:22.132 --> 09:24.632
They deserve to lose everything.

09:24.715 --> 09:27.799
And I deserve to have
all their stuff.

09:27.882 --> 09:30.424
You could just make new things.

09:30.507 --> 09:33.174
Why would I waste my time,

09:33.257 --> 09:36.007
when I can just take
whatever I want

09:36.090 --> 09:38.465
and then kill whoever had them?

09:38.549 --> 09:39.924
[chuckles]

09:41.007 --> 09:42.549
Look at my map.

09:42.632 --> 09:44.299
From here to Braila.

09:44.382 --> 09:48.965
That land and those villages
and towns belong to old men.

09:49.049 --> 09:50.215
All of them.

09:50.299 --> 09:52.382
And I'm going to take them.

09:52.465 --> 09:57.674
This castle belonged
to a stupid, evil old man.

09:58.674 --> 09:59.882
I took it.

09:59.965 --> 10:02.382
The land from here to Braila,

10:02.465 --> 10:05.132
ruled by stupid old men.

10:05.215 --> 10:10.049
Devastated by one single
stupid old man.

10:11.424 --> 10:12.924
There for the taking.

10:13.007 --> 10:16.799
And will you be happy
when you have all that?

10:18.382 --> 10:20.840
Just look at this.

10:22.132 --> 10:23.882
Look.

10:23.965 --> 10:28.090
Do you know how many regional
vampire rulers died at Braila?

10:28.174 --> 10:30.715
I didn't know
I had to count them.

10:30.799 --> 10:32.799
Well, you should.

10:32.882 --> 10:34.507
It was a lot.

10:34.590 --> 10:36.424
These are just the ones
I'm certain of.

10:37.757 --> 10:39.174
[Lenore]
These little flags?

10:39.257 --> 10:40.715
[Carmilla]
That's right.

10:40.799 --> 10:43.715
All these regions
without direct vampire rule.

10:43.799 --> 10:47.465
Just waiting for someone
to take control.

10:47.549 --> 10:51.215
Surely their underlings will
raise someone up into command.

10:51.299 --> 10:54.424
Unless we were there first.

10:54.507 --> 10:56.507
Why would we do that?

10:56.590 --> 10:58.674
This is the world, Lenore.

11:00.132 --> 11:03.382
We could take the entire world
for our own.

11:04.590 --> 11:06.382
Wouldn't you want that?

11:09.549 --> 11:11.340
I don't know.

11:11.424 --> 11:14.965
The "sweet little girl" act
doesn't work on me, Lenore.

11:15.049 --> 11:16.882
Try again.

11:16.965 --> 11:18.132
I really don't know.

11:18.215 --> 11:21.965
I...I never thought
about anything that big before.

11:22.049 --> 11:23.590
Start.

11:23.674 --> 11:25.507
Answer my question first.

11:26.507 --> 11:28.257
Will you be happy

11:28.340 --> 11:30.674
when you have all this?

11:36.465 --> 11:40.049
The first part of my life
was men taking things from me.

11:41.840 --> 11:44.174
And then I took their lives.

11:44.257 --> 11:45.924
And their things.

11:46.007 --> 11:48.382
And their homes.

11:48.465 --> 11:50.174
And then we took Styria.

11:50.257 --> 11:52.882
After which
we formed our little enclave.

11:52.965 --> 11:55.007
We tried not to do more harm.

11:55.090 --> 11:56.924
We tried to make a home.

11:57.007 --> 11:58.882
And when the wolf people
came from the north,

11:58.965 --> 12:00.424
and the armies
from the west,

12:00.507 --> 12:02.465
and every other bastard
came for us.

12:03.715 --> 12:05.049
And we asked for help.

12:06.549 --> 12:08.965
What did the rest
of the vampire world say?

12:09.049 --> 12:11.924
"Bloody women," they said.

12:12.007 --> 12:15.340
"Let them die," they said.

12:15.424 --> 12:18.632
So I'm going to take everything
from everybody.

12:19.715 --> 12:21.465
I was in Dracula's castle.

12:21.549 --> 12:23.965
I went there to see
what I could get out of it.

12:24.049 --> 12:25.507
Get some more power
for myself.

12:25.590 --> 12:27.965
Some more security for us.

12:28.049 --> 12:31.382
What I found was him
and his people just fucking it up.

12:31.465 --> 12:32.924
And I saw, right there,

12:33.007 --> 12:34.549
that I could take the world away
from him

12:34.632 --> 12:36.340
and have it for myself!

12:36.424 --> 12:37.632
[grunts]

12:38.424 --> 12:39.840
The world, Lenore!

12:44.049 --> 12:46.299
Will I be happy
when I've done that?

12:47.299 --> 12:48.632
I don't know.

12:49.715 --> 12:52.090
I don't know if I even care.

12:53.882 --> 12:56.132
But I will have everything
that they had.

12:56.215 --> 12:59.090
And they will all be dead.

13:00.424 --> 13:03.340
I will have the world I want,
Lenore,

13:03.424 --> 13:04.674
and that...

13:06.007 --> 13:07.590
that will be enough.

13:07.674 --> 13:10.507
Having everything
will be enough.

13:10.590 --> 13:12.215
Having the world.

13:13.507 --> 13:15.424
And all of them being dead.

13:16.715 --> 13:19.715
Is this what it was all for?

13:21.299 --> 13:23.799
What on earth did you think
this was all about?

13:24.965 --> 13:26.132
[hammer clinks on metal]

13:26.215 --> 13:27.632
[sizzling and crackling]

13:38.715 --> 13:40.299
I think he finished his hammer.

13:51.424 --> 13:53.049
[Sypha]
Well, this won't be terrible,

13:53.132 --> 13:54.757
for one night.

13:54.840 --> 13:57.424
[Trevor] Look, it's even got
an attractive window.

13:57.507 --> 13:59.174
In the roof.

13:59.257 --> 14:01.174
Perfect.
Sleeping under starlight.

14:03.132 --> 14:05.465
[Trevor]
And targeted by bird shit.

14:05.549 --> 14:07.965
[Sypha] I haven't seen
a single bird since we got here.

14:08.049 --> 14:09.507
-Really?
-[wood creaking]

14:09.590 --> 14:11.674
I can hear something
up in the rafters.

14:21.840 --> 14:23.299
Oh, shit.

14:23.382 --> 14:24.799
[creature growling]

14:27.715 --> 14:29.007
[snarling]

14:29.090 --> 14:30.382
[Trevor]
Here we go again.

14:30.465 --> 14:31.924
Try not to burn the barn down

14:32.007 --> 14:33.257
while we're in it.

14:34.340 --> 14:35.715
I did that one time.

14:36.715 --> 14:37.924
[roars]

14:38.007 --> 14:39.715
One time was enough.

14:39.799 --> 14:42.257
[Sypha]
It had a giant spider in it.

14:43.424 --> 14:44.590
[grunts]

14:44.674 --> 14:45.924
It wasn't giant.

14:47.840 --> 14:49.965
-[roars]
-It was ten feet tall.

14:53.424 --> 14:55.549
Maybe eight.

14:55.632 --> 14:58.132
So, what, eight feet tall
isn't giant?

15:01.049 --> 15:02.340
Fuck me.

15:02.424 --> 15:03.924
These bastards again.

15:04.007 --> 15:06.299
They're very good,
aren't they?

15:07.299 --> 15:08.840
They're annoying.

15:08.924 --> 15:11.007
And young.

15:11.090 --> 15:12.465
[Varney]
I suppose.

15:13.632 --> 15:15.507
[Ratko]
Pretty.

15:15.590 --> 15:17.757
Smooth skin.

15:17.840 --> 15:19.674
What, did you want to nip down
there and marry them?

15:19.757 --> 15:21.007
[hissing]

15:21.090 --> 15:23.549
I want to wear their skin.

15:26.924 --> 15:28.799
[groans]

15:28.882 --> 15:30.799
[creature roars]

15:30.882 --> 15:32.132
[grunts]

15:35.674 --> 15:37.882
Are you sure you don't want me
to set fire to things?

15:39.382 --> 15:41.424
I'm thinking it might
be an option now.

15:41.507 --> 15:43.590
[creatures snarling]

15:43.674 --> 15:44.924
[grunts]

15:46.340 --> 15:48.132
[snarling]

15:54.215 --> 15:55.382
[squeals]

15:57.924 --> 15:59.174
[grunts]

16:06.215 --> 16:08.132
[both grunt and whimper]

16:13.715 --> 16:15.090
[grunts]

16:24.757 --> 16:25.757
[Sypha]
Whoa!

16:27.340 --> 16:28.215
Whoa!

16:41.424 --> 16:43.507
-[grunts]
-[squeals]

16:44.799 --> 16:46.132
[groans]

16:52.299 --> 16:53.840
[groaning]

16:55.882 --> 16:57.465
[grunting]

17:01.215 --> 17:02.465
[roars]

17:03.674 --> 17:05.049
[yells]

17:06.507 --> 17:08.549
[screams]

17:19.799 --> 17:21.424
-[snarling]
-[grunts]

17:40.215 --> 17:41.757
[grunts]

17:47.382 --> 17:49.840
[grunting]

18:07.757 --> 18:09.549
[panting]

18:20.090 --> 18:21.549
Thanks.

18:21.632 --> 18:25.257
We somehow managed
to walk right into that one.

18:25.340 --> 18:29.007
It wasn't for you.
The trap was for us.

18:29.090 --> 18:30.924
I'm Trevor Belmont.

18:31.007 --> 18:33.590
This is Sypha Belnades.

18:33.674 --> 18:37.590
Zamfir. Head guard to the
Underground Court of Targoviste.

18:37.674 --> 18:39.007
The what?

18:39.090 --> 18:40.715
The ruling family
of Targoviste

18:40.799 --> 18:43.215
survived Dracula's
first assault.

18:43.299 --> 18:45.382
But, later, the vampires
and night creatures came,

18:45.465 --> 18:46.757
and it was safer to move them

18:46.840 --> 18:48.799
into the catacombs
under the city.

18:48.882 --> 18:50.632
I'm amazed anyone's still alive,

18:50.715 --> 18:52.507
let alone the royal family.

18:52.590 --> 18:55.424
I run the resistance
against the devils.

18:55.507 --> 18:59.340
Hell itself has attempted
to curse our golden city,

18:59.424 --> 19:02.090
but we will not allow it.

19:02.174 --> 19:04.590
[Trevor]
I'm sorry about your people.

19:04.674 --> 19:06.215
[Sypha]
We are grateful for your aid.

19:06.299 --> 19:07.924
They died for the Court.

19:09.424 --> 19:11.549
Well, they did die.

19:11.632 --> 19:14.049
They were your friends,
were they not?

19:15.882 --> 19:17.715
[Sypha] We have been
following signs of some plot

19:17.799 --> 19:19.340
to return Dracula to Earth.

19:19.424 --> 19:21.674
Does this mean
anything to you?

19:21.757 --> 19:24.799
There's a nest of vampires
in the city who wish it.

19:24.882 --> 19:27.007
They are trying to find
the Underground Court,

19:27.090 --> 19:30.590
to ransack its many magical
treasures for their cause.

19:30.674 --> 19:33.424
[Trevor] We would be interested
in seeing this court.

19:33.507 --> 19:35.382
[Sypha]
To evaluate the threat.

19:36.549 --> 19:37.924
We would be delighted

19:38.007 --> 19:40.090
to have you join
the royal struggle.

19:40.174 --> 19:41.757
Well, good.

19:41.840 --> 19:44.257
Help us save Targoviste.

19:44.340 --> 19:45.715
Gladly.

19:45.799 --> 19:47.049
But not yet.

19:47.132 --> 19:48.840
I cannot take you to the court

19:48.924 --> 19:51.132
until I am certain
I can trust you.

19:52.257 --> 19:53.715
[creaking]

19:58.257 --> 19:59.632
Oh, shit.

20:05.549 --> 20:09.090
[Sypha]
Well, she was...interesting.

20:09.174 --> 20:11.757
You mean a little crazy.

20:12.424 --> 20:14.007
Oh, yes.

20:14.090 --> 20:15.882
[Trevor]
You poor bastards.

20:16.882 --> 20:19.632
-What are you doing?
-Nothing.

20:19.715 --> 20:22.549
Oh, I know you're not
robbing the dead.

20:22.632 --> 20:24.549
Absolutely not.

20:26.507 --> 20:28.424
Hmm. Hmm.

20:36.340 --> 20:38.382
And I've seen enough
glowing rocks for a while.

